CaseTeamRole.name: CaseTeamRole
CaseTeamRole.description: Represents a case team role. Every case team member has a role on a case, such as “Customer Contact” or “Case Manager.”

AccessLevel.description: A value that represents the type of access granted to the target Group for cases. The possible values are: None Read Edit

Name.description: The name of the case team role.

PreferencesVisibleInCSP.description: Indicates whether or not the case team role is visible to Customer Portal users.
